  line
obj_root_law_sections_28_ja:
  sectionId (49802)
  sectionNo 28JA.
  orderNo 41
  title `Qualifications, terms and conditions of service of Chairperson.`
  content `Omitted by ibid., s. 19 (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_ja_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00003_199455_1517807323698&sectionId=49802&sectionno=28JA.&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00003_199455_1517807323698
obj_root_law_sections_28_ja_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28_k:
  sectionId (16591)
  sectionNo 28K
  orderNo 42
  title `Appeals to Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_k_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_k_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00003_199455_1517807323698&sectionId=16591&sectionno=28K&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00003_199455_1517807323698
obj_root_law_sections_28_k_content:
  string
  line `^1[28K. Appeals to Tribunal.--(1) Any person aggrieved by an order of the eviction officer under this`
  line `Chapter may, within fifteen days from the date of such order, prefer an appeal to the ^2[High Court]:`
  line
  line `Provided that the ^3[High Court] may entertain any appeal after the expiry of the said period of fifteen days,`
  line `but not after the period of thirty days from the date aforesaid, if it is satisfied that the appellant was`
  line `prevented by sufficient cause from filing the appeal in time.`
  line
  line ^4*****
obj_root_law_sections_28_k_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act of 43 of 2003, s. 8 (w.e.f. 1-7-2004).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 33 of 2021, s. 19, for Tribunal in such form as may be prescribed (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 33 of 2021, s. 19, for Tribunal (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  line
  line `4. Sub-sections (2), (3), (4) and (5) omitted by s. 19, ibid. (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
obj_root_law_sections_28_l:
  sectionId (16592)
  sectionNo 28L
  orderNo 43
  title `Procedure and powers of Tribunal`
  content `Omitted by The Tribunals Reforms Act, 2021 (33 of 2021), s. 19 (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_l_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00003_199455_1517807323698&sectionId=16592&sectionno=28L&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00003_199455_1517807323698
obj_root_law_sections_28_l_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28_m:
  sectionId (16593)
  sectionNo 28M
  orderNo 44
  title `Finality of orders`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_m_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_m_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00003_199455_1517807323698&sectionId=16593&sectionno=28M&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00003_199455_1517807323698
obj_root_law_sections_28_m_content:
  string
  line `^1[28M. Finality of orders.--Subject to the provisions of this Act, every order made by an eviction`
  line `officer ^2*** under this Chapter shall be final and shall not be called in question in any suit,`
  line `application, execution or other proceeding and no injunction shall be granted by any court or other`
  line `authority in respect of any action taken or intended to be taken in pursuance of any power conferred by or`
  line `under this Chapter.]`
obj_root_law_sections_28_m_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act of 43 of 2003, s. 8 (w.e.f. 1-7-2004).`
  line
  line `2. The words “or the Tribunal” omitted by s. 19, ibid. (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
obj_root_law_sections_28_n:
  sectionId (16594)
  sectionNo 28N
  orderNo 45
  title `Offences under this Chapter.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_n_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_n_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00003_199455_1517807323698&sectionId=16594&sectionno=28N&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00003_199455_1517807323698
obj_root_law_sections_28_n_content:
  string
  line `^1[28N. Offences under this Chapter.--(1) Whoever, unlawfully occupies any airport premises, shall`
  line `be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to six years and with fine.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever fails to comply with any order of the eviction officer or the ^2[High Court] under this Chapter`
  line `shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to seven years and with fine.`
  line
  line `(3) If any person who has been evicted from any airport premises under this Chapter again occupies`
  line `the premises without authority for such occupation, he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term`
  line `which may extend to ten years and with fine.`
  line
  line `(4) The court may, while convicting a person under sub-section (3), make an order for evicting that`
  line `person summarily and he shall be liable to such eviction without prejudice to any other action that may be`
  line `taken under this Chapter.]`
obj_root_law_sections_28_n_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act of 43 of 2003, s. 8 (w.e.f. 1-7-2004).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 33 of 2021, s. 19, for “Tribunal” (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
obj_root_law_sections_28_o:
  sectionId (16595)
  sectionNo 28-O
  orderNo 46
  title `Offences by companies`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_o_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act of 43 of 2003, s. 8 (w.e.f. 1-7-2004).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00003_199455_1517807323698&sectionId=16595&sectionno=28-O&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00003_199455_1517807323698
obj_root_law_sections_28_o_content:
  string
  line `^1[28-O. Offences by companies.--(1) Where any offence under this Chapter has been committed by a`
  line `company, every person who, at the time the offence was committed, was directly in charge of, and was`
  line `responsible to, the company for the conduct of the business of the company, as well as the company, shall`
  line `be deemed to be guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished`
  line `accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment provided in this Chapter, if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge`
  line `or he has exercised all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where an offence under this Chapter has`
  line `been committed by a company and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the consent or`
  line `connivance of, or is attributable to, any neglect on the part of, any director, manager, secretary or other`
  line `officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall also be deemed to be guilty`
  line `of that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation --For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means any body corporate and includes a firm or other association of individuals;`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) "director", in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm.]`
obj_root_law_sections_28_p:
  sectionId (16596)
  sectionNo 28P
  orderNo 47
  title `Congizance of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_p_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act of 43 of 2003, s. 8 (w.e.f. 1-7-2004).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00003_199455_1517807323698&sectionId=16596&sectionno=28P&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00003_199455_1517807323698
obj_root_law_sections_28_p_content:
  string
  line `^1[28P. Cognizance of offences.--No court shall take cognizance of any offence under this Chapter`
  line `except on a complaint made by the Authority, eviction officer or any other officer authorised by it and no`
  line `court inferior to that of a Metropolitan Magistrate or a Judicial Magistrate of the first class shall try any`
  line `offence punishable under this Chapter.]`
obj_root_law_sections_28_q:
  sectionId (16597)
  sectionNo 28Q
  orderNo 48
  title `Power to obtain information.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_q_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act of 43 of 2003, s. 8 (w.e.f. 1-7-2004).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00003_199455_1517807323698&sectionId=16597&sectionno=28Q&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00003_199455_1517807323698
obj_root_law_sections_28_q_content:
  string
  line `^1[28Q. Power to obtain information.--If the eviction officer has reason to believe that any persons`
  line `are in an unauthorised occupation of any airport premises, he or any other officer authorised by him in`
  line `this behalf may require those persons or any other person to furnish information in relation to the names`
  line `and other particulars of the persons in occupation of the airport premises and every person so required`
  line `shall be bound to furnish the information in his possession.]`
obj_root_law_sections_28_r:
  sectionId (16598)
  sectionNo 28R
  orderNo 49
  title `Officers, etc., to aid and assist`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_r_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act of 43 of 2003, s. 8 (w.e.f. 1-7-2004).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00003_199455_1517807323698&sectionId=16598&sectionno=28R&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00003_199455_1517807323698
obj_root_law_sections_28_r_content:
  string
  line `^1[28R. Officers, etc., to aid and assist.--It shall be the duty of all the officers of the Government`
  line `including police officers and any local authority to aid and assist the eviction officer or other officers of`
  line `the Authority in the discharge of their functions under this Chapter.]`
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (16599)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 50
  title `Submission of annual report.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00003_199455_1517807323698&sectionId=16599&sectionno=29&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00003_199455_1517807323698
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Authority shall, as soon as may be after the end of each`
  line `financial year, prepare and submit to the Central Government in such form as may be prescribed a report`
  line `giving an account of its activities during that financial year and the report shall also give an account of the`
  line `activities which are likely to be undertaken by the Authority during the next financial year.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government shall cause such report to be laid before both Houses of Parliament as`
  line `soon as may be after it is submitted.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (16600)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 51
  title Delegation
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00003_199455_1517807323698&sectionId=16600&sectionno=30&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00003_199455_1517807323698
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `The Authority may, by general or special order in writing, delegate to the`
  line `Chairperson or any other member or to any officer of the Authority, subject to such conditions and`
  line `limitations, if any, as may be specified in the order, such of its powers and functions under this`
  line `Act, (except the powers under section 42) as it may deem necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (16601)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 52
  title `Authentication of orders and other instruments of the Authority`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00003_199455_1517807323698&sectionId=16601&sectionno=31&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00003_199455_1517807323698
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `All orders and decisions`
  line `of the Authority shall be authenticated by the signature of the Chairperson or any other member`
  line `authorised by the Authority in this behalf and all other instruments executed by the Authority shall be`
  line `authenticated by the signature of an officer of the Authority authorised by it in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (16602)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 53
  title `Officers and employees of the Authority to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00003_199455_1517807323698&sectionId=16602&sectionno=32&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00003_199455_1517807323698
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `All officers and employees of`
  line `the Authority shall, while acting or purporting to act in pursuance of the provisions of this Act or of any`
  line `rule or regulation made thereunder, be deemed to be public servants within the meaning of section 21 of`
  line `the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (16603)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 54
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes `1. The words “or the Chairperson of the Tribunal” omitted by Act 33 of 2021, s. 19 (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00003_199455_1517807323698&sectionId=16603&sectionno=33&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00003_199455_1517807323698
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall`
  line `lie against the Authority or any member or any officer or other employee of the Authority ^1*** for anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done in pursuance`
  line `of this Act or of any rule or regulation made thereunder or for any damage sustained by any aircraft or`
  line `vehicle in consequence of any defect in any of the airports, civil enclaves, heliports, airstrips, aeronautical`
  line `communication stations or other things belonging to or under the control of the Authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (16604)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 55
  title `Custody and disposal of lost property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00003_199455_1517807323698&sectionId=16604&sectionno=34&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00003_199455_1517807323698
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `Subject to such regulations as the Authority may make`
  line `in this behalf, the authority shall provide for securing the safe custody and restoration of any property`
  line `which, while not in proper custody, is found on any premises belonging to the Authority or under its`
  line `overall control or in any aircraft on any such premises.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (16605)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 56
  title `Provisions relating to income-tax.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00003_199455_1517807323698&sectionId=16605&sectionno=35&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00003_199455_1517807323698
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `For the purposes of the Income-tax Act, 1961 (43 of 1961)`
  line `or any other enactment for the time being in force relating to income-tax or any other tax on income,`
  line `profits or gains, the Authority shall be deemed to be a company within the meaning of the Income-tax`
  line `Act, 1961 and shall be liable to tax accordingly on its income, profits and gains.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (16606)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 57
  title `Power of the Authority to undertake certain works.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00003_199455_1517807323698&sectionId=16606&sectionno=36&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00003_199455_1517807323698
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `The Authority may undertake to carry`
  line `out on behalf of any person any works or services or any class of works or services on such terms and`
  line `conditions as may be agreed upon between the Authority and the person concerned.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (16607)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 58
  title `Power to issue directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00003_199455_1517807323698&sectionId=16607&sectionno=37&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00003_199455_1517807323698
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Authority or any officer specially authorised by it in this`
  line `behalf may, from time to time, by order, issue directions, consistent with the provisions of the Aircraft`
  line `Act, 1934 (22 of 1934) and the rules made thereunder, with respect to any of the matters specified in`
  line `clauses (f), (h), (i), (j), (k), (m), (p), (qq) and (r) of sub-section (2) of section 5 of that Act, to any person`
  line `or persons engaged in aircraft operations or using any airports, heliport, airstrip or civil enclave, in any`
  line `case where the Authority or the officer is satisfied that in the interests of the security of India or for`
  line `securing the security of the aircraft it is necessary to do so.`
  line
  line `(2) Every direction issued under sub-section (1) shall be complied with by the person or persons to`
  line `whom such direction is issued.`
  line
  line `(3) If any person wilfully fails to comply with any direction issued under this section, he shall be`
  line `punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months or with fine which may extend`
  line `to five thousand rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (16608)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 59
  title `Power of the Central Government to temporarily divest the Authority of the management of any airport.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00003_199455_1517807323698&sectionId=16608&sectionno=38&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00003_199455_1517807323698
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `(1) If, at any time, the Central Government is of opinion that in the public interest it is`
  line `necessary or expedient so to do, it may, by order, direct the Authority to entrust the administration,`
  line `management or similar other functions of any airport, heliport, airstrip, civil enclave, aeronautical`
  line `communication station, or any other agency or department of any airport, heliport, airstrip civil enclave or`
  line `aeronautical communication station with effect from such date and to such person as may be specified in`
  line `the order and the Authority shall be bound to comply with such direction:`
  line
  line `Provided that before an order is made under this sub-section the Authority shall be given a reasonable`
  line `opportunity of being heard in the matter.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the management of any airport, heliport, airstrip, civil enclave or aeronautical`
  line `communication station or any other agency or department thereof is entrusted to any person specified`
  line `under sub-section (1) (hereafter referred to in this section as the authorised person), the Authority shall`
  line `cease to exercise and discharge all its powers and functions under this Act in relation to such airport,`
  line `heliport, airstrip, civil enclave or aeronautical communication station or any other agency or department`
  line `thereof and such powers and functions shall be exercised and discharged by the authorised person in`
  line `accordance with the instructions, if any, which the Central Government may give to the authorised person`
  line `from time to time:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such power or function as may be specified by the Central Government by a general`
  line `or special order shall be exercised or discharged by the authorised person except with the previous`
  line `sanction of the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) An order made under sub-section (1) shall, unless rescinded, be in operation for a period of six`
  line `months from the date on which the management of the airport, heliport, airstrip, civil enclave or`
  line `aeronautical communication station or any other agency or department thereof is entrusted to the`
  line `authorised person:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may extend such period for a further period or periods not`
  line `exceeding eighteen months.`
  line
  line `(4) During the operation of an order made under sub-section (1), it shall be competent for the Central`
  line `Government to issue, from time to time, such directions to the Authority as are necessary to enable the`
  line `authorised person to exercise the powers and discharge the functions of the Authority under this Act in`
  line `relation to the airport, heliport, airstrip, civil enclave or aeronautical communication station, or any other`
  line `agency or department thereof the management of which has been entrusted to him and in particular to`
  line `transfer any sum of money from the fund of the Authority to the authorised person for the management of`
  line `the airport, heliport, airstrip, civil enclave or aeronautical communication station or any other agency or`
  line `department thereof and every such direction shall be complied with by the Authority.`
  line
  line `(5) On the cesser of operation of any order made under sub-section (1) in relation to any airport,`
  line `heliport, airstrip, civil enclave or aeronautical communication station, or any other agency or department`
  line `thereof the authorised person shall cease to exercise and perform the powers and functions of the`
  line `authority under this Act in relation to such airport, heliport, airstrip, civil enclave or aeronautical`
  line `communication station or any other agency or department thereof and the Authority shall continue to`
  line `exercise and perform such powers and functions in accordance with the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(6) On the cesser of operation of any order made under sub-section (1) in relation to any airport,`
  line `heliport, airstrip, civil enclave or aeronautical communication station, or any other agency or department`
  line `thereof the authorised person shall hand over to the Authority any property (including any sum of money`
  line `or other asset) remaining with him in connection with the management of such airport, heliport, airstrip,`
  line `civil enclave or aeronautical communication station.`
  line
  line `(7) Anything done or any action taken lawfully by the authorised person in relation to any airport,`
  line `heliport, airstrip, civil enclave or aeronautical communication station or any other agency or department`
  line `thereof during the period of operation of an order made under sub-section (1) shall be deemed to have`
  line `been done or taken by the Authority and shall be binding on the Authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (16609)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 60
  title `Power of the Central Government to supersede the Authority`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00003_199455_1517807323698&sectionId=16609&sectionno=39&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00003_199455_1517807323698
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `(1) If, at any time, the Central`
  line `Government is of opinion--`
  line
  line `(a) that on account of a grave emergency, the Authority is unable to discharge the functions and`
  line `duties imposed on it by or under the provisions of this Act; or`
  line
  line `(b) that the Authority has persistently made default in complying with any direction issued by the`
  line `Central Government under this Act or in the discharge of the functions and duties imposed on it by or`
  line `under the provisions of this Act and as a result of which default the financial position of the`
  line `Authority or the administration of any airport, heliport, airstrip, civil enclave or aeronautical`
  line `communication station has deteriorated; or`
  line
  line `(c) that circumstances exist which render it necessary in the public interest so to do,`
  line
  line `the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, supersede the Authority for such`
  line `period, not exceeding six months, as may be specified in the notification:`
  line
  line `Provided that before issuing a notification under this sub-section for the reasons mentioned in`
  line `clause (b), the Central Government shall give a reasonable opportunity to the Authority to show cause`
  line `why it should not be superseded and shall consider the explanations and objections, if any, of the`
  line Authority.
  line
  line `(2) Upon the publication of a notification under sub-section (1) superseding the Authority,--`
  line
  line `(a) all the members shall, as from the date of supersession, vacate their offices as such;`
  line
  line `(b) all the powers, functions and duties which may, by or under the provisions of this Act, be`
  line `exercised or discharged by or on behalf of the Authority, shall until the Authority is re-constituted`
  line `under sub-section (3), be exercised and discharged by such person or persons as the Central`
  line `Government may direct;`
  line
  line `(c) all property owned or controlled by the Authority shall, until the Authority is re-constituted`
  line `under sub-section (3), vest in the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) On the expiration of the period of supersession specified in the notification issued under`
  line `sub-section (1), the Central Government may--`
  line
  line `(a) extend the period of supersession for such further term not exceeding six months, as it may`
  line `consider necessary; or`
  line
  line `(b) re-constitute the Authority by fresh appointment and in such case the members who vacated`
  line `their offices under clause (a) of sub-section (2) shall not be deemed disqualified for appointment:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may, at any time before the expiration of the period of`
  line `supersession, whether as originally specified under sub-section (1) or as extended under this`
  line `sub-section, take action under clause (b) of this sub-section.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government shall cause a notification issued under sub-section (1) and a full report of`
  line `any action taken under this section and the circumstances leading to such action to be laid before both`
  line `Houses of Parliament at the earliest opportunity.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (16610)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 61
  title `Power of the Central Government to issue directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00003_199455_1517807323698&sectionId=16610&sectionno=40&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00003_199455_1517807323698
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `(1) Without prejudice to the foregoing`
  line `provisions of this Act, the Authority shall, in the discharge of its functions and duties under this Act, be`
  line `bound by such directions on questions of policy as the Central Government may give in writing to it from`
  line `time to time:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Authority shall, as far as practicable, be given opportunity to express its views`
  line `before any direction is given under this sub-section.`
  line
  line `(2) The decision of the Central Government whether a question is one of policy or not shall be final.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government may, from time to time, issue directions to the Authority regarding the`
  line `discharge of any functions to it under clause (e) of sub-section (3) of section 12 and the Authority shall be`
  line `bound to comply with such directions.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (16611)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 62
  title `Power to make rules`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00003_199455_1517807323698&sectionId=16611&sectionno=41&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00003_199455_1517807323698
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules for carrying out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for--`
  line
  line `(a) the period of notice as may be given by the Central Government to terminate the appointment`
  line `of any part-time member of the Authority under clause (b) of proviso to`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 5;`
  line
  line `(b) the conditions of service of the members of the Authority under sub-section (2) of section 5;`
  line
  line `(c) the period of notice as may be given by any member to resign his office under sub-section (3)`
  line `of section 5;`
  line
  line `(d) the provisions subject to which officers and other employees may be appointed by the`
  line `Authority and the category of officers to be appointed after approval of the Central Government under`
  line `the proviso to sub-section (1) of section 10;`
  line
  line `(e) the provisions subject to which the Authority may manage the airports, civil enclaves and`
  line `aeronautical communication stations under sub-section (1) of section 12;`
  line
  line `^1[(ee) ^2[the rate of development fees in respect of airports other than major airports and] the`
  line `manner of regulating and utilising the fees under section 22A;]`
  line
  line `(f) the manner in which the Authority may invest its funds under clause (b) of sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 24;`
  line
  line `(g) the form in which the annual statement of accounts shall be prepared by the Authority under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 28:`
  line
  line `^1[(gi) the other manner of serving notice under sub-section (3) of section 28C;`
  line
  line `(gii) the other manner of serving notice under sub-section (4) of section 28C;`
  line
  line `(giii) the principles of assessment of damages under sub-section (2) of section 28G;`
  line
  line `(giv) the rate of simple interest under sub-section (3) of section 28G;`
  line
  line `(gv) any other matter under clause (c) of section 28H;`
  line
  line ^3*****
  line
  line `(h) the form in which a report giving an account of its activities shall be prepared and submitted`
  line `by the Authority to the Central Government under sub-section (1) of section 29; and`
  line
  line `(i) any other matter which is to be, or may be, prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act of 43 of 2003, s.10 (w.e.f. 1-7-2004).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 27 of 2008, s. 54 and the Schedule, for the rate of development fees and (w.e.f. 1-1-2009).`
  line
  line `3.Clauses (gvi), (gvii), (gviii) and (gix) omitted by Act 33 of 2021, s. 19 (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (16612)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 63
  title `Power to make regulations`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00003_199455_1517807323698&sectionId=16612&sectionno=42&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00003_199455_1517807323698
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Authority may make regulations not inconsistent with this`
  line `Act and the rules made thereunder to provide for all matters for which provision is necessary or expedient`
  line `for the purpose of giving effect to the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such regulations may provide`
  line for--
  line
  line `(a) the time and places of the meetings of the Authority and the procedure to be followed for the`
  line `transaction of business including the quorum at such meetings under sub-section (1) of section 8;`
  line
  line `(b) the conditions of service and the remuneration of officers and other employees to be`
  line `appointed by the Authority under sub-section (2) of section 10;`
  line
  line `(c) the construction of residential accommodation for the officers and other employees appointed`
  line `by the Authority under clause (e) of sub-section (3) of section 12;`
  line
  line `(d) the storage or processing of goods in any warehouse established by the Authority under`
  line `clause (g) of sub-section (3) of section 12 and the charging of fees for such storage or processing;`
  line
  line `(e) the contracts or class of contracts which are to be sealed with the common seal of the`
  line `Authority and the form and manner in which a contract may be made by the Authority under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 21;`
  line
  line `(f) the custody and restoration of lost property and the terms and conditions under which lost`
  line `property may be restored to the persons entitled thereto under section 34;`
  line
  line `(g) the disposal of any lost property in cases where such property is not restored;`
  line
  line `(h) securing the safety of aircraft, vehicles and persons using the airport or civil enclave and`
  line `preventing danger to the public arising from the use and operation of aircraft in the airport or civil`
  line enclave;
  line
  line `(i) preventing obstruction within the airport or civil enclave for its normal functioning;`
  line
  line `(j) prohibiting the parking or waiting of any vehicle of carriage within the airport or civil enclave`
  line `except at places specified by the Authority;`
  line
  line `(k) prohibiting or restricting access to any part of the airport or civil enclave;`
  line
  line `(l) preserving order within the airport or civil enclave and preventing damage to property therein;`
  line
  line `(m) regulating or restricting advertising within the airport or civil enclave;`
  line
  line `(n) requiring any person, if so directed by an officer appointed by the Authority in this behalf, to`
  line `leave the airport or civil enclave or any particular part of the airport or civil enclave; and`
  line
  line `(o) generally for the efficient and proper management of the airport or civil enclave.`
  line
  line `(3) Any regulation made under any of the clauses (h) to (o) (both inclusive) of sub-section (2) may`
  line `provide that a contravention thereof shall be punishable with fine which may extend to five hundred`
  line `rupees and in the case of a continuing contravention with an additional fine which may extend to twenty`
  line `rupees for every day during which such contravention continues after conviction for the first such`
  line contravention.
  line
  line `(4) No regulation made by the Authority under this section shall have effect until it has been approved`
  line `by the Central Government and published in the Official Gazette.`
  line
  line `(5) Notwithstanding anything contained in this section, the first regulations under this Act shall be`
  line `made by the Central Government and shall have effect on being published in the Official Gazette.`
  line
  line `(6) The first regulations framed under sub-section (5) shall remain in force until such time the`
  line `Authority has made regulations and they are published in the Official Gazette.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (28932)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 64
  title `Rules and regulations to be laid before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00003_199455_1517807323698&sectionId=28932&sectionno=43&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00003_199455_1517807323698
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `Every rule and every regulation made`
  line `under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it`
  line `is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more`
  line `successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the`
  line `successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or regulation, as`
  line `the case may be, or both Houses agree that the rule or regulation, as the case may be, should not be made,`
  line `the rule or regulation shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of`
  line `anything previously done under that rule or regulation.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (28933)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 65
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00003_199455_1517807323698&sectionId=28933&sectionno=44&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00003_199455_1517807323698
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government may, by general or special order published in the Official Gazette, make`
  line `such provisions not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act as appear to it to be necessary or`
  line `expedient for the removal of the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made after the expiration of one year from the commencement of`
  line `this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under sub-section (1) shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before`
  line `each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised`
  line `in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the order or both Houses agree that the order should not be made, the order shall thereafter have effect`
  line `only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification`
  line `or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that order.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (28934)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 66
  title Repealed..
